---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Experience — Pipo Leong"
  description="Career timeline of Pipo Leong"
>
  <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold">Work Experience</h1>
  <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
    A chronological view of my roles and impact.
  </p>

  <ol class="relative mt-6 border-s border-black/10 dark:border-white/10">
    <li class="ms-6 pb-10 last:pb-0">
      <span
        class="absolute -start-2.5 mt-1 flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-brand text-white ring-8 ring-white/70 dark:ring-gray-950"
      >
        <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-white/90"></span>
      </span>
      <div
        class="flex flex-col gap-1 sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline sm:justify-between"
      >
        <h3 class="font-semibold">Software Developer</h3>
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Aug 2020 — Aug 2025</span>
      </div>
      <p
        class="mt-1 flex items-center gap-3 italic text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"
      >
        <img
          src="https://genwhy.com.my/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/genwhy-logo-crop.jpg"
          alt="Genwhy Sdn Bhd logo"
          width="24"
          height="24"
          class="h-6 w-6 rounded ring-1 ring-black/10 dark:ring-white/20 bg-white object-contain"
          decoding="async"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        Genwhy sdn bhd · Ara Damansara, Petaling Jaya
      </p>
      <ul
        class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
      >
        <li>
          Migrated legacy systems from CodeIgniter 1 to CodeIgniter 4, improving
          maintainability and performance.
        </li>
        <li>
          Implemented CI/CD pipelines with GitHub for automated testing and
          deployment.
        </li>
        <li>
          Integrated AI, AWS, and Alibaba Cloud; containerized environments
          using Docker.
        </li>
        <li>
          Designed and deployed RFID-enabled solutions for tracking and
          automation.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <span class="badge">CodeIgniter</span>
        <span class="badge">Docker</span>
        <span class="badge">GitHub Actions</span>
        <span class="badge">AWS</span>
        <span class="badge">Alibaba Cloud</span>
        <span class="badge">RFID</span>
        <span class="badge">AI/ML</span>
        <span class="badge">CI/CD</span>
        <span class="badge">Laravel</span>
        <span class="badge">PHP</span>
        <span class="badge">Node.js</span>
        <span class="badge">Javascript</span>
        <span class="badge">Vue.js</span>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="ms-6 pb-10 last:pb-0">
      <span
        class="absolute -start-2.5 mt-1 flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-brand text-white ring-8 ring-white/70 dark:ring-gray-950"
      >
        <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-white/90"></span>
      </span>
      <div
        class="flex flex-col gap-1 md:flex-row md:items-baseline md:justify-between"
      >
        <h3 class="font-semibold">
          Sales & Technical Support Executive (Part Time)
        </h3>
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">2019</span>
      </div>
      <p
        class="mt-1 flex items-center gap-3 italic text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"
      >
        <img
          src="https://www.gloo.com.my/image/catalog/Logo/gloo_black.png"
          alt="Gloo logo"
          width="24"
          height="24"
          class="h-6 w-6 rounded ring-1 ring-black/10 dark:ring-white/20 dark:bg-white object-contain"
          decoding="async"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        Microsoft (Onsite at SNS Network, Gloo) · Lowyat, Bukit Bintang
      </p>
      <ul
        class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
      >
        <li>
          Assisted customers with PC troubleshooting, setup, and technical
          inquiries to improve user experience.
        </li>
        <li>
          Promoted sales through product demonstrations, merchandising, and
          customer engagement.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <span class="badge">Windows</span>
        <span class="badge">PC Hardware</span>
        <span class="badge">Troubleshooting</span>
        <span class="badge">Customer Service</span>
      </div>
    </li>

    <li class="ms-6 pb-10 last:pb-0">
      <span
        class="absolute -start-2.5 mt-1 flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-brand text-white ring-8 ring-white/70 dark:ring-gray-950"
      >
        <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-white/90"></span>
      </span>
      <div
        class="flex flex-col gap-1 md:flex-row md:items-baseline md:justify-between"
      >
        <h3 class="font-semibold">Sales & Technical Support Executive</h3>
        <span class="text-sm text-gray-500">Dec 2017 — May 2018</span>
      </div>
      <p
        class="mt-1 flex items-center gap-3 italic text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"
      >
        <img
          src="https://www.tmt.my/data/editor/All_TMT_Logo_White.png"
          alt="Thunder Match Technology (TMT) logo"
          width="24"
          height="24"
          class="h-6 w-6 rounded ring-1 ring-black/10 dark:ring-white/20 bg-gray-900 p-0.5 object-contain"
          decoding="async"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        Thunder Match Technology (TMT) · Mid Valley, KL
      </p>
      <ul
        class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
      >
        <li>
          Explained product features, pricing, and demonstrated usage to help
          customers make informed decisions.
        </li>
        <li>
          Handled transactions, maintained stock displays, and ensured accurate
          product labeling.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <span class="badge">Retail Tech</span>
        <span class="badge">POS</span>
        <span class="badge">Customer Support</span>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>
</BaseLayout>
